    <thetext>Description of problem:
With lxpanel-0.8.2-2.fc25.x86_64 the battery applet reports correct charge information.  With 

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):


How reproducible:
Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1.Use a machine that has a battery (a laptop, for instance)
2.Install lxpanel 0.8.2-2.fc25
2.Enable the battery applet.
3.Confirm that the battery applet shows the state of the battery.
4.dnf update lxpanel
5.log out and back in to run the new lxpanel
6.notice that the battery applet now shows a completely dead battery, no matter what state the battery is actually in.

Actual results:
Battery shown as 0%

Expected results:
Battery state reflects actual charge of the battery.

Additional info:
This might only happen on specific laptops.  Mine is an Asus X551M</thetext>
